Looking at `observation/queries.ts:54-57`:

```typescript
const targets: ObserveTargetRecord[] = [];
if (input.relatedRecord) targets.push(input.relatedRecord);
if (input.relatedRecords) targets.push(...input.relatedRecords);
```

There's no semantic difference — both end up in the same `targets` array, and each gets an `observes` edge. `relatedRecord` (singular) is the original field for the common single-target case. `relatedRecords` (plural) was added later to support linking multiple entities without breaking existing callers.

In this fix, `relatedRecord` links the decision (the primary target) and `relatedRecords` links the task (the additional target). Both produce identical `observes` edges in the graph.

